snippet.textDisplay:
So I just wanted to point out a couple of things about you hamster care. First of all, that cage is waaay to small. I'm pretty sure it's not even the minimum size required tbh, witch really shows that you have done absolutely no research before getting your hamster. Also your cage has bars which combined with the fact that the cage is extremely small will probably lead to him hurting his nose on the bars.

Also, once again becuse the cage is so small you really dont have any space for toys or enrichment which will ofcorse leade to him being bored.
Lastly a wire wheel is very bad for your hamsters feet since they can get bumble foot from it.

Honestly I cant understand how some people get a animal without doing the slightest effort to give them a good life. Just a quick google search will tell you exactly how bad your hamster care is. Also videos like this will influence your audience into thinking this care is normal and not at all completely wrong. You ever getting a hamster was just completely wrong from the start.
